Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, salt, and pepper; cook and stir until garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in shrimp and 1 teaspoon garam masala; cook until shrimp turn pink, about 4 minutes. Transfer shrimp to a bowl; add remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil, red onion, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, and lemon juice. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Mix mango, cucumber, celery, cilantro, and orange zest into the shrimp mixture. Chill for 1 hour before serving.